items.name: Sunlight
items.description:
üåû Sunlight üåû

Bask in the warm glow of Sunlight! Add drama and depth to your images with beautiful dappled streaks of light and shadow from sun passing through leaves or windows. Or add mystery and wonder with the bluer tones of moonlight üåõ!

Tips

No trigger words are necessary. Like any style model, overlong negative prompts will decrease the effect. I highly recommend combining with LowRA or similar darkening LoRAs. Or use img2img to create zones of darkness or color. Great for portraits, landscapes, and still life.

Check each version's notes for more tips and info.

modelVersions.name: deliberate sunlight v0.1
modelVersions.description:
v0.1

This version should be considered a prototype. For now I'm releasing the version that's a fine-tuning of the excellent Deliberate v2. This gives you all the flexibility and style of that wonderful mix along with the new capabilities and style of my fine-tuning.

If you like this prototype and want to see it improve, please let me know and please share your images!

Tips

For this v0.1, you can increase the style effect with "light and shadow". CFG up to 7 usually looks great, but I prefer 5.

Training notes

Trained on just over a hundred hand-captioned photos. About 60% people and faces, 20% places, 20% things. Just 900 steps at lr=1.2e-6, using EveryDream. I tried many more, but this was the best result.

items.name: Tifa (Final Fantasy VII) LoRA
items.description:
Tifa from Final Fantasy VII, trained on animefull.

Around 0.7 weight works well. Trigger word is 'tifa ff7'. Adding 'tank top', 'black skirt', 'suspender skirt', 'midriff', 'black thighhighs', and 'red gloves' can all help with generating her outfit.

This model CANNOT generate Tifa's official alternate outfits. They were not included in the dataset, because I was making this model as a joke in the first place (check the comments on my Robin LoRA if you feel you need context, not that it helps). It still generates her in her default outfit and can do other, unofficial outfits just fine. If you're looking for a model that can generate multiple official outfits, I'd recommend checking out this LoRA by Lykon.

Tifa is my favorite character from Final Fantasy VII! I mean, come on! Who doesn't love her potent combination of physical strength and emotional depth? A true martial arts master with a heart as big as the Planet, she embodies both a fearless warrior and a compassionate friend.

I've always admired her tenacity, resilience and most importantly, her unwavering loyalty towards her friends. Every time she takes the battlefield, with her fists at the ready, it's like watching poetry in motion! Those Limit Breaks of hers? Absolutely electrifying! From Beat Rush to Final Heaven, each one is more thrilling than the last.

This is a LoRA for Lewis Griffin from American Guy üòâ

It was trained on ~130 pictures with pretty rough prompt pruning.

Most of the training images were ( nude üò≥) so clothing is pretty tough. I wanted to try and keep the style mostly the same for this version, but next version will most likely have more images.

I use it at 0.8 strength but I'm sure full is probably fine too. I'm not a master proompter yet so I do like to have it a little weaker for *creativity*

Yes, obviously I know the name of the show and the character. Lewis and American Guy are some cheeky little jokes.
